        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(plugins): pin HTTP route registry during gateway bootstrap",
        "body": "Refs #94572 (partial mitigation)\n\n## Summary\n\nThree partial mitigations for workspace plugin HTTP routes not being wired into the running gateway:\n\n1. **Bootstrap pin**: Add `pinActivePluginHttpRouteRegistry` to the bootstrap pin function\n2. **Runtime loader**: `surface: \"active\"` now pins HTTP routes in `installStandaloneRegistry`\n3. **Gateway lookup**: Return `getPluginRegistryState()?.activeRegistry` in `getPluginRouteRegistry`\n\nThese changes ensure HTTP routes are pinned in both bootstrap and runtime-loaded paths, and the gateway's route lookup can see the active registry. The full fix requires a gateway-owned deferred runtime attachment mechanism (outside this PR's scope).\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/gateway/server-plugin-bootstrap.ts`: Add `pinActivePluginHttpRouteRegistry`\n- `src/plugins/runtime/standalone-runtime-registry-loader.ts`: Pin HTTP routes in `\"active\"` surface\n- `src/gateway/server.impl.ts`: Use active registry in `getPluginRouteRegistry`\n\n## Risk\n\n- [x] Backwards compatible\n- [x] No global state modification",
        "branch": "fix/issue-94572-plugin-http-routes",
